1
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:20,433
I'm sorry for punishing you
for something you didn't do.

2
00:00:20,567 --> 00:00:22,167
I won't do it again, okay?

3
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,267
I don't know anything!

4
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,033
Let me go! I don't know
anything!

5
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,567
You didn't do this alone!

6
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:29,700
Who are you working with?

7
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,600
Hey! Stop that!

8
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:34,700
Put your gun down.

9
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:38,367
You are my first
and last love.

10
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:42,667
I don't want to be with anyone
else but you forever.

11
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:46,533
I want to spend the rest
of my life loving you.

12
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,500
Take your mask off.

13
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:50,900
I know it's you, Rina.

14
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:52,400
I just want to see your face.

15
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:54,333
I won't ever forget this place.

16
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:56,700
We met on this island.

17
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,867
We fell for each other
on this island.

18
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,833
And we also found our way back
to each other on this island.

19
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:09,800
Next time we come back to
an island, we will say our vows.

20
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:11,900
Because that's where we're
going to get married.

21
00:01:12,033 --> 00:01:14,500
I've been preparing for this,
Rina.

22
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,100
You can't fool me anymore.

23
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,800
You can't hurt me anymore.

24
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:19,233
Come closer, and I'll slap
your face!

25
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:20,833
Wait! Shut up!

26
00:01:24,233 --> 00:01:26,000
Run! Get in the car!

27
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:28,733
Amanda and Lucho set us up.

28
00:01:28,867 --> 00:01:31,833
We have to hide before we think
of getting revenge.

29
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:35,633
How will I tell Victor and Red
that I should go into hiding?

30
00:01:35,767 --> 00:01:37,867
Do whatever you want!
I'm leaving!

31
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,700
What else are you hiding
from me?

32
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:42,000
We have a warrant of arrest
for Rina Ramos.

33
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:43,733
She needs to come with us
to the precinct.

34
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:44,967
Why are you with them?

35
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:47,033
Because I witnessed
what happened.

36
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:49,567
Don't touch me! Don't touch me!

37
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:50,800
Don't worry. I'll be there.

38
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:51,800
What is this?

39
00:01:51,933 --> 00:01:53,233
Justice is served.

40
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:54,767
You had Mama Rina arrested.

41
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:57,700
She has a warrant of arrest
for frustrated murder

42
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,633
and two counts
of frustrated homicide.

43
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:02,900
Are you letting hatred
consume you?

44
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,833
Karma did this to her, Eden.

45
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:09,500
Whatever Rina is reaping
right now,

46
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:11,700
it's because of what she sowed.

47
00:02:18,767 --> 00:02:20,500
That's enough.

48
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:21,867
There's nothing we can do now.

49
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,500
We have to obey the law.

50
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:24,867
- Red, let her go.
- Mom, Dad!

51
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,867
No, no, no!

52
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,400
- I'm not coming with them.
- No!

53
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:28,633
- No!
- I'm not coming with you.

54
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:29,800
Let my mom go!

55
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:32,200
- I'm not coming with you!
- No!

56
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:34,033
No! Let my mom go!

57
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:35,233
Red, Red. Stop it.
That's enough.

58
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:36,633
- No!
- We can't do anything about it.

59
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:37,867
My mom is innocent!

60
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,200
- We have to obey the law!
- She didn't do anything wrong!

61
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,800
I don't want to go.

62
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:44,233
- Ma'am, let's go.
- Red, let her go.

63
00:02:44,367 --> 00:02:45,233
We can't do anything about it.

64
00:02:45,367 --> 00:02:46,267
- We have to abide by the law!
- No!

65
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,267
Mom!

66
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,033
- Mom, don't worry.
- We'll follow her.

67
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,867
We'll get you out of this, Mom.

68
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:55,800
Can I bring my daughter
home first?

69
00:02:55,933 --> 00:02:58,167
No, Ma'am. You have to come
with us.

70
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,867
You're going? Who's going home?

71
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,100
You are not going home!

72
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:03,567
Mom!

73
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,367
Bring her to the police station!

74
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:06,667
Bring her now!

75
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,500
You're working with Raul!

76
00:03:08,633 --> 00:03:10,167
You two planned this!

77
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:13,000
Ma'am, I'm innocent.

78
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:15,300
Bring that criminal
to the precinct!

79
00:03:15,433 --> 00:03:16,633
You're a murderer!

80
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:18,467
You killed my son!

81
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,467
Red, we'll follow her.

82
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,700
Mama Rina, you have
to be strong.

83
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:52,533
Why is Amanda doing this to me?

84
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:57,067
She's the one who did
something wrong,

85
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:59,000
but she's making me the bad guy.

86
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:03,000
I didn't do anything wrong.

87
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:08,033
She's just taking revenge.

88
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:11,667
Do you know the person
accusing you?

89
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,167
I don't know them.

90
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,967
Amanda's making all of this up.

91
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,300
Everything...

92
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,000
Everything is scripted.

93
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:26,233
Red, you know I'm not
a bad person, right?

94
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:28,200
Look, I can't even hurt a fly.

95
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,500
You know that.

96
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,867
I'm not capable of committing
a crime.

97
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,667
I didn't do anything.

98
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,800
Mom, okay.

99
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,467
Don't worry. We'll talk
to our lawyer.

100
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,067
We'll get you out of here, okay?

101
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,933
Red, please. Do everything
you can.

102
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:43,567
- Yeah.
- I can't stay another day here.

103
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,700
I'm going to die here.

104
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:45,733
I don't like this place.

105
00:04:45,867 --> 00:04:48,067
I can't stay here.

106
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,467
I'm sorry.

107
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,567
I know this is all my mom's
fault.

108
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:54,067
She's so mad at me.

109
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,867
That's why she's doing this.

110
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,333
She hates all of us.

111
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:04,267
She wants me to get a taste
of what she's been through.

112
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:07,233
She's taking revenge.

113
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:10,567
She's taking revenge because
of what happened before.

114
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:16,433
Just hang on, Mom.

115
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:31,567
This is it.

116
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:34,667
It's time to celebrate.

117
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:38,067
You put Rina in jail.

118
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,433
You're slowly getting
your revenge.

119
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,867
What's wrong?

120
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,633
You don't look happy.

121
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:56,200
I don't know.

122
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,700
I want to be happy.

123
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,233
But I feel like something
is missing.

124
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:07,900
Eden didn't give Rina
a condemning look.

125
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:09,567
That's what I want to see,
Lucho.

126
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:12,100
How come it didn't happen?

127
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:15,633
I want her to see that I'm
a better mother than Rina.

128
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:24,567
Don't worry.

129
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:27,133
Your daughter will realize
that someday.

130
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:29,533
She might not realize it now.

131
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:30,700
Just be patient.

132
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:33,800
It will happen.

133
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,100
I hope so.

134
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:40,300
I really hope so.

135
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:45,967
I'm sure my sister is not
capable of doing that.

136
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:47,500
I don't believe that, Auntie.

137
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:50,300
Mama Rina went to jail
because of mom.

138
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:51,567
Wait.

139
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:56,267
I'll take care of this.

140
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:59,467
Mom, let Mama Rina
get out of jail

141
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,800
while I still have some respect
left for you.

142
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:05,267
I didn't put your Mama Rina
in jail.

143
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,267
The police caught her
doing a crime.

144
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,567
My mom didn't do
anything wrong.

145
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,833
That's what she said.

146
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:12,467
- You set her up!
- How?

147
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,667
Mom, can't you do anything
better?

148
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:18,600
Did you really turn into
an evil person?

149
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:21,700
Are you blinded, Eden?

150
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,667
If there's an evil person
around here, it's not me.

151
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,767
It's your fake mother!

152
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:29,467
She's been doing illegal
business.

153
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,567
And the police just caught up
with her.

154
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:35,467
Did you know that your mom
is a loan shark?

155
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,867
She lends out money and
threatens those people

156
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,533
who owe her money.

157
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:43,567
She put a lot of interest on top
of what people owed her.

158
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,633
And if they can't pay her
what they owe,

159
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:49,233
she has her evil brother
beat them up.

160
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,900
Your Uncle Zandro.

161
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:55,733
And unfortunately,
some get killed.

162
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,700
You're a liar.

163
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:05,533
You're just making that up.

164
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:06,867
My mom is not capable
of doing that.

165
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,133
That's what you thought.

166
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:11,467
You're just taking revenge
because she put you in jail!

167
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,600
Mom, I'm begging you
to stop this.

168
00:08:14,733 --> 00:08:17,967
I know you went through
hard times before.

169
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,100
I know it was painful.

170
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:23,300
Because I went through
the same thing.

171
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:25,333
But you've gone too far!

172
00:08:25,467 --> 00:08:27,300
Please, stop!

173
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:29,067
Don't worry, Eden.

174
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,500
You'll thank me in the end.

175
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:34,533
Because I will reveal
Rina's true personality.

176
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:39,100
She's been good to me.

177
00:08:39,233 --> 00:08:42,633
You're the one who has changed.

178
00:08:42,767 --> 00:08:46,633
Do you think we don't know that
you've been sending us threats?

179
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:50,833
Remember the funeral flower
you sent me?

180
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:53,400
Because I'm dead to you!

181
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:58,600
And you've been calling and
threatening us on the phone.

182
00:08:58,733 --> 00:09:02,033
And do you remember the fetus
you sent me?

183
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:05,267
You are the reason
I lost my baby!

184
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,567
Why would I do that to you?

185
00:09:08,933 --> 00:09:11,367
Why would I want you to lose
your baby?

186
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,700
If there's anyone who could
really love you,

187
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,167
it's me, your mom.

188
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:16,933
You're not my mom anymore!

189
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:19,400
Mama Rina is my mom now.

190
00:09:19,533 --> 00:09:23,067
Because she took care of me
when you weren't there!

191
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:28,033
Go ahead! Stay with
that wicked family!

192
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,133
Keep this in mind.

193
00:09:29,267 --> 00:09:30,667
You will regret it if you
don't listen to me...

194
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,633
if you don't believe me.

195
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,000
Go ahead! Stay with your family!

196
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,700
Go on!

197
00:09:38,367 --> 00:09:39,800
Go ahead!

198
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:03,667
Hey, Victor.

199
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:08,033
That's enough.

200
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:10,367
You're brave.

201
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,400
You have a lot of nerve
to attack me.

202
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:16,233
You set my wife up!

203
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:19,333
Don't you know your hustler wife
up until now?

204
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:21,367
Listen, Victor.

205
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:27,433
Rina's a veteran moneylender.

206
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:32,233
And she put a high interest
on top of it.

207
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:34,233
And if the clients can't pay
her...

208
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:41,200
That's how cruel your wife is.

209
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:44,000
Do you think I'll believe you?

210
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:45,833
I've known Rina for a long time.

211
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:49,233
We were business rivals.

212
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:53,433
Rina's a big time in this
business world.

213
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:56,900
Rina and I are similar, Victor.

214
00:10:57,033 --> 00:11:01,500
If our clients don't pay
what they owe us,

215
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:04,600
we'll make them pay
with their life.

216
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:12,800
You owe me money, right?

217
00:11:12,933 --> 00:11:14,967
Now you know what will happen
to you if you don't pay me

218
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,767
what you owe.

219
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:20,433
Let's go.

220
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:48,600
I can't do what Eden
is accusing me of.

221
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,633
I didn't send her those things
to threaten her.

222
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:54,767
Who could have done that?

223
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:56,400
I don't know!

224
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,967
They brainwashed her.

225
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:05,867
You see, she thinks
I'm the bad guy now.

226
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:09,133
I don't think I can still
reason with her.

227
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:11,333
Just give Eden more time.

228
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:15,133
And you also have to think
if what you're doing is right.

229
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,633
Is what I did wrong?

230
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:20,267
Rina is a horrible person.

231
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,667
She has to pay for her crimes.

232
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,567
That's not true!

233
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:29,367
Amanda's just accusing me.

234
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,067
Mom, why do you have frustrated
murder and frustrated homicide

235
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,100
cases against you?

236
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:38,567
Because your Uncle Zandro shot
two police officers.

237
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,900
It was an act of self-defense,
okay?

238
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:43,267
I had nothing to do with it.

239
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,733
It's not my fault.

240
00:12:44,867 --> 00:12:46,300
Why are they accusing me?

241
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:49,167
That's the reason there's
a frustrated homicide.

242
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:51,867
But I'm not guilty.
I'm the victim here.

243
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Okay, relax, Mom. Relax.

244
00:12:54,133 --> 00:12:55,300
I haven't talked to Dad yet.

245
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,233
But I talked to the lawyer
already.

246
00:12:57,367 --> 00:12:59,333
He said we could post bail.

247
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:00,967
You'll get out of here.

248
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,667
Everything will be all right,
Mama Rina.

249
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,433
Just remember, we're always here
for you.

250
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:08,767
We won't judge you.

251
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:12,200
And we can prove to the court
you're innocent.

252
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,067
Yes, of course!

253
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,933
I can prove that.

254
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:21,833
I'm worried she might try
to take you away from us, Eden.

255
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:25,167
Mom, it's not going to happen.

256
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,667
I'm going to fight for her.

257
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,833
I know, Red. But my point is...

258
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:36,000
we don't have a right to her.

259
00:13:36,133 --> 00:13:40,133
Eden is seeing it from a
different perspective, Amanda.

260
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:44,767
She thinks you're bullying Rina.

261
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,067
What about me?

262
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,000
Didn't they bully me before?

263
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:51,267
I was innocent,
but they punished me.

264
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,500
It's different today.

265
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:57,233
Dindi, she did something wrong.

266
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,433
And now she's acting like
a victim.

267
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:06,100
Amanda, why don't you
just let fate take place?

268
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:07,300
You know what I mean?

269
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:11,000
Let Rina pay for her crimes
at the right time.

270
00:14:11,133 --> 00:14:13,800
And let Eden come home
on her own terms.

271
00:14:13,933 --> 00:14:15,867
Like people always say,
time will reveal.

272
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:20,667
I can't just leave
everything to fate.

273
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:24,700
I did that before, and look
at what happened to me.

274
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:29,133
I won't just wait and see
what fate will send my way.

275
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,533
I'm going to fight.

276
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:33,767
I will do something to get
my daughter back.

277
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,167
I have to do something.

278
00:14:37,467 --> 00:14:42,033
Knowing Amanda, she might try
to sue us for kidnapping.

279
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:46,167
She will do everything just
to get revenge.

280
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,367
But I chose to stay with Red.

281
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:50,767
He didn't force me.

282
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:55,067
She's not a minor anymore, Mom.

283
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,433
But we have no legal ties
with her.

284
00:14:57,567 --> 00:15:01,533
Unless, of course,
you two get married.

285
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:08,067
But up until that time, Amanda
is still your legal guardian.

286
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,233
Because she's your parent.

287
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:19,433
Sorry, okay? I don't want
to sound pushy.

288
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:23,500
But we've been planning for you
to get married, right?

289
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:28,467
I mean, that's where your
relationship is going anyway.

290
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:38,900
I want both of you to be happy.

291
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,233
The two of you don't deserve
this.

292
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:48,067
The two of you have nothing to
do with my issues with Amanda.

293
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:52,067
You both deserve to be happy.

294
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:55,233
The last thing that the two
of you deserve is to be included

295
00:15:55,367 --> 00:15:57,167
in all this mess.
You don't deserve this!

296
00:15:57,300 --> 00:16:00,100
I want you to be happy.

297
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,500
Victor!

298
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,067
Victor, did you bring the money
to bail me out?

299
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:11,733
- Victor!
- Dad!

300
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:13,333
What's the matter?

301
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:15,033
What's wrong?

302
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:17,300
I should be asking you that.

303
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:19,733
What's wrong with you?

304
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:21,667
How can you do this
to Red and me?

305
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:24,567
What did I do? What are you
talking about?

306
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,967
You have an illegal business.

307
00:16:29,267 --> 00:16:31,133
It's true, right?

308
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:33,900
I don't know what you're
talking about, Victor.

309
00:16:34,033 --> 00:16:35,567
You don't know?

310
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,400
Well, I do.

311
00:16:43,233 --> 00:16:46,033
You're lending money illegally.

312
00:16:46,167 --> 00:16:47,733
You're hurting people.

313
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:52,333
You're a horrible person.

314
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,033
Dad. Wait, what's wrong?

315
00:16:54,167 --> 00:16:56,633
What's going on? Why do you want
to hurt mom?

316
00:16:56,767 --> 00:16:58,700
Because she's a liar, Red!

317
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:03,433
We're together, but she's been
lying to me.

318
00:17:03,567 --> 00:17:05,033
She made me look like a fool!

319
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:08,100
Mom, is this true?

320
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:10,433
Don't try to deny it, Rina.

321
00:17:10,567 --> 00:17:13,600
Lucho told me about
your business.

322
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:16,467
And you'll believe him over me?

323
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:19,833
Yes, because you have
the same business.

324
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:22,100
You and Lucho are the same!

325
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:30,967
Victor deserves to know
the truth about his wife.

326
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,500
She will ruin their family...

327
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:36,567
the way she did to my
relationship with my daughter.

328
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:41,300
What are you planning
to do with Eden?

329
00:17:41,433 --> 00:17:46,333
Will you wait for that family
to fall apart

330
00:17:46,467 --> 00:17:48,367
before you take your daughter
back?

331
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,433
I don't want to force her
to come back to me.

332
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:56,900
I want her to come here
of her own free will.

333
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,267
I want her to come back to me.

334
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:08,067
You've been hiding this from me
for a long time, Rina.

335
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:10,567
So please, admit it.

336
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:13,133
And stop lying because you've
been caught already.

337
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:17,433
Okay! Fine! I admit it!

338
00:18:17,567 --> 00:18:21,300
How can you do this to me, Rina?

339
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:24,733
I've been working hard
for this family

340
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:28,100
only to find out you're doing
an illegal business.

341
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:30,533
You disgraced this family!

342
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:31,967
I'm sorry.

343
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,633
I'm sorry, Victor.

344
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:38,267
I had no intention
of doing this.

345
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,500
Our business was doing well
at first.

346
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:41,500
We were only lending money.

347
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:44,400
It's Zandro's fault.

348
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:48,000
We got addicted to it because
we were making a lot of money.

349
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:49,200
We were making a lot of money.

350
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:51,467
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

351
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,033
Am I not giving you
enough money, Rina?

352
00:18:57,367 --> 00:19:00,400
Did I let this family starve?

353
00:19:00,533 --> 00:19:02,100
Rina, tell me.

354
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:05,767
Where did I go wrong as
a provider of this family?

355
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,833
I'm sorry, Victor.

356
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:12,800
I didn't mean to become
a greedy person.

357
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:15,400
I don't have a criminal wife.

358
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:18,967
Victor, I'm sorry!

359
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,200
Red! I'm sorry!

360
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:44,000
I can't believe my mom
can do that.

361
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:51,500
But even if other people
say she's an evil person,

362
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:55,300
she's still a good mother
to my brother and me.

363
00:19:55,433 --> 00:19:56,633
And to you too.

364
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:59,167
Of course, Red.

365
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:01,967
I'm not judging her.

366
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:05,033
I'm just shocked.

367
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:08,200
How can she do that?

368
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:11,333
So, your mom was right.

369
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:31,400
Mom.

370
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:33,300
Now that you know what
kind of person Rina is,

371
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:34,633
I'm here to take you back.

372
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:35,667
Come on.

373
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,267
Let her go.

374
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,500
Mom, I'm not coming with you.

375
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,000
I'm not leaving Red.

376
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:41,000
What?

377
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:42,867
- Get away from her! No!
- Let go of her.

378
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,833
I'm taking my daughter away from
your family.

379
00:20:45,967 --> 00:20:48,200
I'm sorry, Mom. I'm not coming
with you.

380
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:51,533
Eden, you have to come with me.

381
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,033
Let's go.

382
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:56,400
Yenyen is not a child anymore

383
00:20:56,533 --> 00:20:57,967
for you to make decisions
for her.

384
00:20:58,767 --> 00:20:59,633
Who do you think you are?

385
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:00,833
You don't have a right!

386
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:01,933
You're just her boyfriend!

387
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:03,567
I'm her mom.

388
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:04,633
Come on, Yenyen.

389
00:21:04,767 --> 00:21:05,733
Mom, I'm not coming with you.

390
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:06,933
Stop being stubborn!

391
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:09,733
Do you want to stay with these
wicked people?

392
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,533
Why? Are you a good person?

393
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:13,633
Is your husband a good person?

394
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:16,300
You're not related to them!

395
00:21:16,433 --> 00:21:17,967
I'm your parent.

396
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,600
Come with me?

397
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:23,700
Don't you really care
about me anymore?

398
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:26,800
I'm sorry, Mom, but I'm not
leaving Red...

399
00:21:26,933 --> 00:21:29,167
especially his mom.

400
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:31,867
I can't forget all the good
things she did for me

401
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,900
when you abandoned me.

402
00:21:34,033 --> 00:21:36,267
She might be unpleasant
to others,

403
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:39,033
but she's never been
a bad mother.

404
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:43,000
And she's been a good wife.

405
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:45,100
So, I'm sorry.

406
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:46,700
But I'm not coming with you.

407
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,667
Well, I think it's clear now.

408
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:56,033
We've been more of a family
to her compared to you.

409
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:58,100
You can go now.

410
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:03,333
Emma, please accompany
my mom to the gate.

411
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:43,367
Amanda, the way I see you...

412
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,467
You still look dirt poor.

413
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,500
Just dirt poor?

414
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:50,067
What about you?

415
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:54,200
You look like dirt to me.

416
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:55,367
So, what will you do now?

417
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:57,867
Can't you still forgive
your mom?

418
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,533
Of course, I want to forgive
her.

419
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:01,967
But I don't think it's possible
right now.

420
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:05,633
I pray every day that everything
will be okay.

421
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:08,733
I want all of us to become
a family.

422
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:11,733
Did you like my gift?

423
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:17,533
Now, you tell us we stink!

424
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:20,167
It was physical pain.

425
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:22,933
But you, you have to brace
yourself.

426
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:27,867
Because your whole being
will be in pain.

427
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:30,600
What are you talking about?

428
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:35,600
Red and Eden are getting
married.
